verbose_text: The CNS1 region also harbors RA response element, suggesting that RA signaling may potentiate efficient Treg generation in the periphery, especially in the intestine, in which stromal cells and CD103 + dendritic cells (DCs) within mesenteric lymph node (mLN) and intestine express high levels of RA synthesizing the enzyme retinaldehyde dehydrogenase (RALDH2).
